HOUSE BILL No. 1274
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
insurance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 27-2-30 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE AS
2 A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]:
4 Chapter 30. Gun Free Zone Notice
5 Sec. 1. This chapter applies to a property and casualty insurance
6 policy that is issued, delivered, entered into, renewed, or amended
7 after June 30, 2026.
8 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "gun free zone notice" means a
9 written notice stating that firearms or ammunition are prohibited
10 or otherwise restricted.
11 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "insured" means an individual
12 who is entitled to coverage under a property and casualty
13 insurance policy.
14 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "insurer" means an insurance
15 company that issues or delivers a property and casualty insurance
16 policy.
17 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "property and casualty
2026 IN 1274—LS 6187/DI 144

2
1 insurance" means one (1) or more of the types of insurance
2 described in IC 27-1-5-1, Class 2 and Class 3.
3 Sec. 6. An insurer may not require an insured or prospective
4 insured to post or display a gun free zone notice.
5 Sec. 7. An insurer may not do any of the following based on the
6 failure or refusal by an insured or prospective insured to post or
7 display a gun free zone notice:
8 (1) Cancel, refuse to issue, or refuse to renew a property and
9 casualty insurance policy.
10 (2) Modify a premium or an economic incentive for a
11 property and casualty insurance policy.
12 (3) Exclude, deny, or limit coverage under a property and
13 casualty insurance policy.
14 (4) Modify the terms of a property and casualty insurance
15 policy in a manner that is adverse or unfavorable to an
16 insured or prospective insured.
